fields.descriptive_line: Wooden box containing letters, Peacock and Sons Ltd, London, c.1900
fields.physical_description: Box of wood with sliding lid; polished on the outside and with a printed label attached to the lid. Label, printed in colours, shows three chidren playing with the game. Includes stand of plain wood with three ledges to support the letters. On the underside is a label describing how to play the game.
fields.title: The Parlour Spelling Box
